replies.body:
> Varus's story is BASED on the fact that he lost his family, his wife and his child.

The problem is, this story has been done before. It’s not unique, we’ve seen it before to some extent with Shen, Vayne, Yorick, and Kassadin who’ve all lost their family which set them out on a path or goal. Personally I’m glad they’re making Varus distinct, and I applaud Riot for taking the risk to create a publicly gay champion. 

{{sticker:galio-happy}}
